ting between locations’ can become visible even in the basic sense of being recognized as ‘movement’ at all. What ‘counts’ as movement is contextual and depends on perspective: one's position as a ‘true traveller’ is an asset in a world in which the mastering of movement is an unequally distributed and highly valued resource.


